Comment.MultiLanguageText: Above this value flow will be detroked
Bit used for positive trigger transition on Torq Limiting
Calculated limited output value for flow

AttributeList.Text: Written BY Kristopher Gimenez Feb 3,2023 This block is used to control the TD Drill mode
If throttle not disable get speed setpoint
Start Limiting/Destroke pump If torq set is above zero , Actual Torq above 90% of set point for 1 second debounce or Act torq > 97 set right away. Store Output Flow value when Limiting Starts
If torq limiting- in High torq destroke the ouput. - if low torq increase stroke back to setpoint -Otherwise hold. Slew rate are mA/sec. TON increment set to 10ms so unput Slew rate divided by 100
Reset Limiting if: -Drill Torq Pot Set below zero -Pump Output < then Limiting Output( user lowered drill throttle input) and torq below low threshold
Output Limited Flow if Torq Limited or Pump Flow ouput if not limiting
